# ADR-072 Runtime Continuity

- Read in order before implementing: `AGENTS.md`, `docs/SESSION-HANDOFF.md`, `docs/CHANGELOG.md`, `docs/ADR/072-persai-native-multichannel-runtime-replacement.md`, `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`, `docs/API-BOUNDARY.md`, `docs/DATA-MODEL.md`, `docs/TEST-PLAN.md`, then any ADRs referenced by the chosen step.
- Treat `docs/ADR/072-persai-native-multichannel-runtime-replacement.md` as the source of truth for target architecture and implementation order.
- Treat `docs/SESSION-HANDOFF.md` as the source of truth for the latest completed checkpoint and next step.
- Treat `docs/CHANGELOG.md` as the source of truth for what has actually landed.
- If ADR, handoff, changelog, and code disagree, stop and reconcile docs before code changes.
- One session = one smallest executable step or tightly coupled sub-step from ADR-072. Do not expand scope or skip dependencies.
- At session start, identify the highest-priority unfinished step whose dependencies are satisfied and restate: current slice, current step, purpose, likely affected files/modules, and what is out of scope.
- Keep the final architecture fully PersAI-native. Do not preserve OpenClaw request-time compatibility in target-state code.
- Do not keep `openclawBootstrap` / `openclawWorkspace` as long-term runtime truth. Do not reintroduce filesystem-owned session state. Do not put sandbox or heavy agent boot into the ordinary chat path.
- Touch native OpenClaw only if the current step explicitly requires it and a PersAI-side change is insufficient.
- Before ending the session, update `docs/SESSION-HANDOFF.md`, update `docs/CHANGELOG.md` if repo truth changed, update ADR-072 if architecture or plan changed, update the ADR-072 execution ledger, and state the next recommended step.
